.TH VALIDATE-INTAKE-AUTHORING-RECEIPT 1 "July 2026" "intake-authoring-governance 0.1.0"
.SH NAME
validate-intake-authoring-receipt \- validate intake source and output provenance read-only
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B validate-intake-authoring-receipt.sh
--receipt FILE [--repo PATH]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Validates one schema-1.0 intake-authoring receipt, the normalized SHA-256 of
its generated Markdown target, every repository-local source, clarification
state, rendered command markers, delivery authority, and supersession fields.
Inline and external sources remain snapshot-only.
.PP
The command writes no file and grants no authoring, review, implementation, or
remote authority.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --receipt FILE
Path to the JSON receipt.
.TP
.B --repo PATH
Repository root used to resolve relative target and source paths. Defaults to
the current directory.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Print usage.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 for a current valid receipt, 2 for invalid arguments, schema violations,
source or target drift, unsafe content, or a broken prompt contract.
.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
bash scripts/validate-intake-authoring-receipt.sh \
  --receipt specs/intake-authoring-receipts/example.json --repo .
.fi
